message.raw:
Revised installation script with the following changes:
  Installed HDF5 version 1.8.2->1.8.4
  Explicit PyTables installer (rather than just using setup.py 'requires')
    to make sure it is installed **before** the program of interest.
    This will be more important once we upgrade to PyTables 2.2, since
    that version has dependencies that aren't listed in its setup.py,
    and thus must be managed separately (Cython, numexpr, numpy).
  Changed check_version() interface.
  Updated the way versions are extracted from URLs, to allow hyphens in the
    version number (rather than in the program name, as was previously the case)

message.raw:
Added Genome.add_track_continuous method
  This method can be used to create new supercontig datasets, as well as
  extend existing ones along the track column. This makes it replace
  a large amount of the functionality of genomedata-load-data, as
  empty datasets are created automatically at the first call to
  genomedata-open-data.

Genomedata supercontigs are now represented as an Extendible Array (EArray)
to support this expansion on the track dimension.

message.raw:
Added example script directory with random access example
Move tracknames to be file-based instead of chromosome-based, and
  added _set_tracknames_continuous functionality to deal with setting this
  regardless of the implementation. This move makes accessing tracknames
  fast regardless of the number of sequences if the archive is generated with
  default settings (at most 100 files).
Fixed bug in load_seq where the default implementation was dependent upon
  the number of files, not the number of sequences

message.raw:
* Created a uniform interface for loading Genomedata archives, whether they
  are a directory or a single file (untested). This includes calling improving
  the handling of non-context-manager Genome objects by requiring a call
  to Genome.close() when finished.
* Added an option to genomedata-load-seq and genomedata-load
  to specify the Genomedata archive implementation (directory/file).
  Default is directory if number of sequences is at least 100.
